  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6763.61 sitting right in the thick negative gamma zone between 6750-6765 (all major amplifying walls), dealers are forced to buy this rally as they're short gamma in a BREAKOUT regime. The massive negative GEX concentration from 6750-6765 creates a feedback loop where any momentum gets amplified by dealer flow, while 6800 represents the first meaningful resistance where dealers will start selling against the move. Watch for acceleration through 6765 toward 6800, but expect violent rejection if we reach that positive gamma wall without sustained volume.\n\n**Bottom line:** dealers are buying this rally hard, expect momentum to continue toward 6800 resistance.",
